docker file sample

  Here‚Äôs a sample Dockerfile that sets up a basic Apache web server on Ubuntu:

# Use official Ubuntu base image
FROM ubuntu:20.04

# Set environment variable to avoid interactive prompts
ENV DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive

# Update packages and install Apache
RUN apt-get update && \
    apt-get install -y apache2 && \
    apt-get clean

# Copy custom index.html (optional)
COPY index.html /var/www/html/index.html

# Expose port 80
EXPOSE 80

# Start Apache in foreground
CMD ["apachectl", "-D", "FOREGROUND"]
===========================================
üìÑ Optional: index.html
<!-- index.html -->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head><title>Hello from Docker</title></head>
  <body>
    <h1>Apache is running inside a Docker container!</h1>
  </body>
</html>
===========================================
‚ñ∂Ô∏è Build and Run the Docker Image
# Build the image
docker build -t my-apache-image .

# Run a container from the image
docker run -d -p 8080:80 --name my-apache-container my-apache-image
===========================================
Now open your browser and go to: http://localhost:8080
